a.xlink:title: class CityMap This file describes reusable model elements that are used in the bCMS Crisis Management System. It is necessary to have a rudimentary Graphical Information System such as described in this submodel as part of bCMS in order to plan routes and to track where crises are. This file has the necessary classes. * A CityMap contains the precompiled streets and landmarks This must be read in from the database on system initialization
String description Name of landmark (name of fire station, business, address)

class NamedRoad * A named road might have the name of a street, the number of a highway, etc. A RoadSegment can have several names because for example, sometimes several numbered highways share a segment
String direction Most roads have two directions, e.g. North and South
class Location * A Location describes a place such as an intersection, landmark, bend in a road, etc.

class RoadNode * RoadNodes are places where RoadSegments connect. A node with just one incoming and one outgoing is used to handle changes in direction, e.g. as a road turns a corner, changes in speed limit, changes in number of lanes, and other factors. When there is more than one outgoing or incoming, the node represents points where traffic flow can split and join. A crossroads is one type. Entry into a roundabout would be another, Highway merges and exits are other kinds as are parking lots and entries into or out of fire stations.. RoadSegments leaving the city lead to no RoadNode RoadSegments entering the city come from no RoadNode

class RoadSegment * A RoadSegment represents a section of road on which a vehicle can drive. The ends of each segment have been modeled using RoadNodes. Note that distance can be calculated from the speed limit, and locations
Integer currentReportedSpeed Indicator of real-time congestion; 0=blocked
Integer streetNumberAtStart The following are used to determine addresses
class Turn * Turns are used to model illegal turns, e.g. turning left when there is 'no left turn' allowed, or 'no U turn' allowed.
class Route * A route is a plan to get from one location to another It is built by algorithms that traverse the nodes and arcs of the map taking into account speed, congestion, etc.
Integer estimatedTime Time seconds at current flow speeds
